----------------------------------------------
Being Location Independent Isn=E2=80=99t Just a Luxury
----------------------------------------------

Work from anywhere, live anywhere, travel freely.

Digital nomad, location independent, or freed from the tyranny of
geography.

Whatever you call it, it=E2=80=99s definitely a fantastic asset for your
lifestyle.

Now that more people are experiencing remote work, more people
see the possibilities. Maybe you=E2=80=99ve gotten your feet wet with a
flexcation (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/4zu7pwv4elhehvxkk7sx/g3hnhwuednox8pu3/aH=
R0cHM6Ly90aGVrbm93LmRlbnZlcnBvc3QuY29tLzIwMjAvMTIvMDQvZmxleGNhdGlvbi10cmF2Z=
WwtdHJlbmQtY29yb25hdmlydXMtcGFuZGVtaWMvMjQ4NDExLw=3D=3D
), where you travel to somewhere cool for a while to redefine
=E2=80=9Cworking from home.=E2=80=9D

I=E2=80=99ve been location independent for 15 years, although far from
what you would call a nomad. But as we discussed a couple weeks
ago (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/4zu7pwv4elhehvxkk7sx/9qhzhdugqx3nvntz/aH=
R0cHM6Ly9mdXJ0aGVyLm5ldC93b3JraW5nLXRvd2FyZC8=3D
), my plan is to live in different parts of the world on a
more-or-less permanent basis when my kids are out of high school.

While I like to keep things on the positive tip, being
unconstrained by geography has another aspect to it. I see it as
a necessity at this point that my family and I are not tied to
any one country =E2=80=93=E2=80=93 the United States in particular.

For years you=E2=80=99ve heard about the decline of the U.S., especially
on the global leadership front. But the more pragmatic concern is
that the quality of life has dropped (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/4zu7pwv4elhehvxkk7sx/3ohphduqor9v5xcp/aH=
R0cHM6Ly93d3cubnl0aW1lcy5jb20vMjAyMC8wOS8wOS9vcGluaW9uL3VuaXRlZC1zdGF0ZXMtc=
29jaWFsLXByb2dyZXNzLmh0bWw=3D
) in America over the last decade, even as it has risen almost
everywhere else.

Once the pandemic hit, many trends already in motion accelerated
-- including the sentiment that things are going south in the
States. This led Americans who can work virtually to leave the
country in record numbers (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/4zu7pwv4elhehvxkk7sx/n2hohqun8g5e9mf0/aH=
R0cHM6Ly93d3cud2FzaGluZ3RvbnBvc3QuY29tL25hdGlvbmFsL3dlYXJ5LWZyb20tcG9saXRpY=
2FsLXN0cmlmZS1hbmQtYS1wYW5kZW1pYy1zb21lLWFtZXJpY2Fucy1hcmUtZmxlZWluZy10aGUt=
Y291bnRyeS8yMDIwLzExLzAyL2VlNjYwMzhjLWY4NDAtMTFlYS04OWUzLTRiOWVmYTM2ZGM2NF9=
zdG9yeS5odG1s
):

The exodus has been led by parents looking for countries with
open and safe schools and by members of marginalized groups fed
up with institutionalized racism, shaken by the visibility of
white supremacists, and worried about what a Supreme Court swing
to the right will mean for their civil liberties.

Given that these people are often entrepreneurs and other
creative professionals, this only leaves the country in a more
precarious position (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/4zu7pwv4elhehvxkk7sx/reh8h9uq27vnlru6/aH=
R0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjAtMDYtMjkvY29yb=
25hdmlydXMtYnJpbmdzLWFtZXJpY2FuLWRlY2xpbmUtb3V0LWluLXRoZS1vcGVu
):

With its high housing costs, poor infrastructure and transit,
endemic gun violence, police brutality and bitter political and
racial divisions, the U.S. will be a less appealing place for
high-skilled workers to live.

The domino effect then begins:

That in turn will exacerbate some of the worst trends of U.S.
decline -- less tax money means even more urban decay as
infrastructure, education, and social-welfare programs are forced
to make big cuts.

With the national deficit at a staggering $27 trillion, one
wonders how the incredible amount of work that needs to be done
can be accomplished and paid for. And that=E2=80=99s before you factor in
that the nation hasn=E2=80=99t been this politically divided (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/4zu7pwv4elhehvxkk7sx/08hwhgumoxwq66hp/aH=
R0cHM6Ly93d3cucGV3cmVzZWFyY2gub3JnL2ZhY3QtdGFuay8yMDIwLzExLzEzL2FtZXJpY2Eta=
XMtZXhjZXB0aW9uYWwtaW4tdGhlLW5hdHVyZS1vZi1pdHMtcG9saXRpY2FsLWRpdmlkZS8=3D
) since the Civil War.

I can personally understand the desire to stay and turn things
around. But when those who study such things are talking in terms
of not only decline, but potential collapse, well ... there comes
a time when the decision to put your family and yourself first
becomes a no-brainer.

Peter Turchin is a scientist and professor specializing in
cultural evolution and cliodynamics -- the mathematical modeling
and statistical analysis of the dynamics of historical societies.
He=E2=80=99s been warning for a decade that social and political trends
point to an =E2=80=9Cage of discord,=E2=80=9D with unrest and chaos worse t=
han
most Americans have ever experienced (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/4zu7pwv4elhehvxkk7sx/vqh3hmunx4389whw/aH=
R0cHM6Ly93d3cudGhlYXRsYW50aWMuY29tL21hZ2F6aW5lL2FyY2hpdmUvMjAyMC8xMi9jYW4ta=
GlzdG9yeS1wcmVkaWN0LWZ1dHVyZS82MTY5OTMv
):

In 2010, he predicted that the unrest would get serious around
2020, and that it wouldn=E2=80=99t let up until those social and
political trends reversed. Havoc at the level of the late 1960s
and early =E2=80=9970s is the best-case scenario; all-out civil war is
the worst.

According to Turchin, American society is going to get ugly for
the rest of the decade (at minimum). =E2=80=9CIt=E2=80=99s too late,=E2=80=
=9D he
contends, to head off major disruption. It=E2=80=99s going to happen, the
only question is to what degree.

The problems are deep and structural -- not the type that the
tedious process of demo=C2=ADcratic change can fix in time to
forestall mayhem. Turchin likens America to a huge ship headed
directly for an iceberg.

If you find this concerning, you should. If your first impulse is
to blow it off as fanciful, you do so at your own peril. Turchin
is far from alone (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/4zu7pwv4elhehvxkk7sx/l2heh6uo04vwmdsg/aH=
R0cHM6Ly93d3cuYXhpb3MuY29tL3RydW1wLWdlb3JnZS1mbG95ZC1hbWVyaWNhLXNvY2lhbC1jb=
2xsYXBzZS1iNTY2YWU3OC05MDdjLTQxYjctOTkyZC1iZTVlMzM1MjFmYjIuaHRtbA=3D=3D
) in this assessment.

And we haven=E2=80=99t even factored in the effect of massive job losses
and disruption due to the pandemic-accelerated adoption (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/4zu7pwv4elhehvxkk7sx/m2h7h6uog90w6xal/aH=
R0cHM6Ly90aW1lLmNvbS81ODc2NjA0L21hY2hpbmVzLWpvYnMtY29yb25hdmlydXMv
) of AI, automation, and robotics. We=E2=80=99re not on the cusp of the
proverbial perfect storm, we=E2=80=99re already in it.

Look, maybe America survives and comes out of the turmoil better
and stronger (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/4zu7pwv4elhehvxkk7sx/dphehmuq4kwr93al/aH=
R0cHM6Ly93d3cudGhlYXRsYW50aWMuY29tL21hZ2F6aW5lL2FyY2hpdmUvMjAyMC8xMC9tYWtlL=
WFtZXJpY2EtYWdhaW4vNjE1NDc4Lw=3D=3D
). Maybe not. That=E2=80=99s not really the issue.

The issue is, what happens in the meantime? Is this the time of
life to ride something like this out?

What happens if your income is tied to a job in the United
States, and you can=E2=80=99t leave? What if your primary asset is real
estate on American soil, and your money is all in U.S. dollars in
American banks?

Some people are under the incredibly incorrect impression that
the U.S is safe and secure while the rest of the world is scary
and unstable. If you=E2=80=99re willing to set aside that fairy tale, I
think you=E2=80=99ll realize it=E2=80=99s time to rewrite your story when i=
t
comes to both freedom and security.

Do your own research. Take a long hard look at reality. I think
you=E2=80=99ll find that becoming a citizen of the rest of the world
looks like a damn good alternative going forward.

Maybe you think being location independent seems like a really
cool dream that perhaps you=E2=80=99ll pursue. I=E2=80=99d say it=E2=80=99s=
 a much more
pragmatic goal to strive for than that. It might just turn out to
be absolutely crucial.

In other words, it=E2=80=99s time to start coming up with your personal
plan for future freedom. It can be both the fulfillment of a
dream and the prudent thing to do at the same time.

